[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Software deployment and maintenance
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: en_50716_grammar.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document covers the Software Deployment and Maintenance phases for the
railway control and protection system identified below. It is prepared in
accordance with EN 50716:2023, Clauses 9.1 (Software deployment) and 9.2
(Software maintenance), and collects seven output deliverables from Table A.1:

  39. Software Deployment Manual
  40. Deployment Records
  41. Deployment Verification Report
  42. Software Maintenance Plan
  43. Software Change Records
  44. Software Maintenance Records
  45. Software Maintenance Verification Report

BASIC and SIL_1 through SIL_4 fields are taken from EN 50716:2023:
- Table A.1 (doc 43):                          BASIC=HR, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.1 (docs 39, 40, 41, 42, 44, 45):     BASIC=R,  SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.10 (software maintenance techniques, Clause 9.2):
    Impact analysis:             BASIC=R,  SIL_1=HR, SIL_2=HR, SIL_3=M, SIL_4=M.
    Data recording and analysis: BASIC=HR, SIL_1=HR, SIL_2=HR, SIL_3=M, SIL_4=M.

DCR-xxx are software change records; each DCR entry documents a single approved
change from request through implementation and verification closure.

Instructions for use:
- UIDs follow convention: DM-xxx (requirements), DCR-xxx (change records).
- Duplicate DCR entries for each software change.
- Duplicate deployment record blocks in §3 for each deployment instance.
- Delete this instruction block before formal release.
<<<

