[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software Deployment Manual

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Deployment Manual as required by
EN 50716:2023, Clause 9.1 and Table A.1 (document 39). It defines the
procedures and constraints for deploying the software release to the
operational target system, covering pre-deployment checks, loading, post-load
verification, and rollback.
<<<

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Pre-deployment checks and prerequisites

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: DM-010
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Pre-deployment checks and prerequisites
STATEMENT: >>>
The following checks shall be completed and recorded before commencing
software deployment at any site.

Authorisation prerequisites:
  a) Deployment authorisation obtained from <System Owner / Safety Manager>
     for site <site identifier> (reference: <authorisation record ID>).
  b) Maintenance window agreed with operations control: start <HH:MM>,
     end <HH:MM>, date <YYYY-MM-DD>.
  c) Adjacent systems and interfaces notified of planned outage per
     operating procedures <ref>.
  d) The system to be updated is confirmed out of operational service and
     in maintenance mode; no trains or movements permitted in affected area.

Hardware and platform verification:
  e) Target hardware platform: <name, revision> — confirmed to match the
     hardware specification in the release note (VAL-100 / APP-140).
  f) Bootloader version: <version> — confirmed compatible with the software
     release being deployed.
  g) Available non-volatile memory: <n> kB free — sufficient for release
     <SW-REL-xxx / APP-REL-xxx> (requires <n> kB per APP-140 / VAL-100).
  h) Hardware self-test: all on-board diagnostics pass; no active hardware
     faults recorded.

Backup of existing software:
  i) Current software version on target: <version, SHA-256 hash>.
  j) Backup copy saved to <removable medium / server path> and verified
     by hash comparison.
  k) Backup recovery procedure tested on an identical non-live unit:
     <reference to test record>.

Software package integrity:
  l) Deployment package received: <filename>, SHA-256: <hash>.
  m) Hash verified against the release note (<SW-REL-xxx>): <Match confirmed>.
  n) Package is the approved release; no modifications since release sign-off.

Personnel:
  o) Deployment engineer: <Name, qualification reference>.
  p) Supervising safety engineer: <Name, qualification reference>.

Pre-deployment checklist reference: <document ID>
All items above shall be checked and signed off before loading commences.
<<<
