[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software loading procedure

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: DM-020
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Software loading procedure
STATEMENT: >>>
The following procedure shall be followed to load the software onto the target
system. All steps are mandatory; no step may be skipped.

Loading procedure:

  Step 1 — Connect deployment tool:
    Connect <deployment tool name, version> to target via <interface type>.
    Confirm tool reports target hardware identifier <HW-ID> and current
    software version <version>.

  Step 2 — Initiate loading sequence:
    Select deployment package <filename> (hash verified in DM-010, step l).
    Initiate loading via <tool menu path / command>.
    Tool displays progress; do not interrupt or power-cycle during loading.
    Expected loading duration: approximately <n> minutes.

  Step 3 — Verify loading completion:
    Tool reports: "Loading complete. <n> bytes written."
    Tool performs automatic post-write readback CRC; result shall be PASS.
    If readback CRC fails: do not commission; execute rollback (DM-040).

  Step 4 — Apply parameter file (if separate):
    Load parameter file <params_vX.Y.bin> (hash: <SHA-256>) using
    <parameter loading command>.
    Tool confirms: parameter file applied; parameter checksum PASS.

  Step 5 — Power cycle target:
    Remove deployment tool connection.
    Apply controlled power cycle to target: power off for <n> s, then on.
    Observe start-up sequence; confirm no error codes on local display.

  Step 6 — Record loading results:
    Record in deployment record (DM-060): tool output log reference,
    post-write CRC result, parameter file hash, power-cycle timestamp.

Expected duration (all steps): <n> minutes.
Tool output log shall be archived with the deployment record.
<<<
BASIC: R
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
