[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Post-load verification procedure

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: DM-030
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Post-load verification procedure
STATEMENT: >>>
Post-load verification shall be performed immediately after loading (DM-020)
and before returning the system to operational service.

Verification steps:

  Step 1 — Software version check:
    Query target software version via <diagnostic interface / local display>.
    Confirmed version: <vM.N.P-buildNNN> (matches SW-REL-xxx / APP-REL-xxx).
    If version mismatch: execute rollback (DM-040).

  Step 2 — Binary hash verification:
    Read back software binary from target using <deployment tool>.
    Compute SHA-256 hash of read-back binary.
    Compare against release note hash (<hash value>): shall match exactly.
    If hash mismatch: execute rollback (DM-040).

  Step 3 — Start-up self-test:
    Observe target start-up sequence; all on-board self-tests shall report PASS.
    Self-test results visible on <local display / diagnostic port>.
    Any FAIL result: halt commissioning; investigate and execute rollback if
    the cause cannot be resolved.

  Step 4 — Commissioning tests:
    Execute the commissioning test sequence defined in the deployment guide
    reference (VAL-120 / APP-140).
    Required tests:

      Test ID | Description                              | Pass criterion
      --------|------------------------------------------|-------------------
      CT-001  | <System start-up and mode transition>    | <mode: OPERATIONAL>
      CT-002  | <External interface IF-EXT-01 handshake> | <LINK-UP within n s>
      CT-003  | <Safety function: output state at start> | <fail-safe state>
      CT-004  | <Watchdog refresh cycle>                 | <no reset in n cycles>
      CT-005  | <Diagnostic read-back>                   | <version = vM.N.P>

    All commissioning tests shall show PASS before the system is returned
    to operational service. Any FAIL: halt; investigate; execute rollback if
    required.

  Step 5 — Notify control and restore service:
    Notify operations control that commissioning is complete and system is
    ready for return to service.
    Record time of service restoration in deployment record (DM-060).

Post-load verification checklist reference: <document ID>
<<<
BASIC: R
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Testing
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 9.1 and Table A.1, doc 39 – Software Deployment Manual.

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Rollback procedure

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: DM-040
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Rollback procedure
STATEMENT: >>>
The rollback procedure shall be executed whenever a deployment step fails
or any post-load verification check (DM-030) cannot be resolved. Rollback
restores the system to the previously verified operational software version.

Rollback triggers:
  - Post-write CRC fails (DM-020, Step 3).
  - Software version mismatch (DM-030, Step 1).
  - Binary hash mismatch after read-back (DM-030, Step 2).
  - Start-up self-test FAIL that cannot be resolved (DM-030, Step 3).
  - Any commissioning test FAIL that cannot be resolved (DM-030, Step 4).
  - Deployment engineer or supervising safety engineer judgement.

Rollback procedure:

  Step 1 — Confirm system is in maintenance mode and out of service.

  Step 2 — Load backup software from the backup medium created in DM-010
    (step j) using <deployment tool>.
    Backup file: <filename>, SHA-256: <hash from DM-010, step i>.
    Follow loading steps DM-020 (Steps 1–5) using the backup package.

  Step 3 — Perform post-load verification (DM-030) on the restored backup
    version.

  Step 4 — If backup restoration is successful:
    Record rollback in deployment record (DM-060): trigger, steps taken,
    backup version restored, post-load verification result.
    Notify deployment engineering team; raise incident report <IR-xxx>.
    Do not return system to service until incident reviewed and resolved.

  Step 5 — If backup restoration also fails:
    System shall remain out of service.
    Escalate immediately to <Safety Manager / System Engineer>.
    Hardware fault investigation may be required.

The failed deployment package shall be quarantined pending investigation.
No re-attempt of the original deployment package without engineering
approval and root-cause analysis.
<<<
BASIC: R
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 9.1 and Table A.1, doc 39 – Software Deployment Manual.

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Safety constraints during deployment

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: DM-050
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Safety constraints during deployment
STATEMENT: >>>
The following safety constraints are mandatory during all deployment activities
and shall be included in site safety briefings.

System state constraints:
  a) The system under deployment shall be confirmed out of operational service
     before any software loading activity commences.
  b) No partial deployment is permitted: the complete software release package
     shall be loaded in a single operation; loading of individual files or
     modules separately is not allowed.
  c) The system shall not be returned to operational service until all post-load
     verification steps (DM-030) are completed with PASS results.
  d) If deployment is interrupted for any reason, rollback (DM-040) shall be
     executed before leaving the site; no system shall be left in an
     indeterminate software state.

Personnel constraints:
  e) Deployment shall be performed only by personnel holding the deployment
     authorisation qualification <qualification code>.
  f) A supervising safety engineer independent of the deployment engineer
     shall be present at site for all deployments at SIL ≥ 2.
  g) Both deployment engineer and supervising engineer shall sign the
     deployment record (DM-060) before the system is returned to service.

Environmental and operational constraints:
  h) Deployment shall not be commenced during adverse environmental conditions
     that could cause power interruption (e.g., lightning storm).
  i) Deployment tool laptop / workstation shall be powered from a stable supply
     with UPS backup or battery power during loading.
  j) Communications shall be maintained with operations control throughout
     the deployment window.

Constraint reference: <document ID of site safety plan / operating procedures>
These constraints supersede any contradictory site-specific instructions.
<<<
BASIC: R
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 9.1 and Table A.1, doc 39 – Software Deployment Manual.

