UID: DM-080
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Deployment verification scope and method
STATEMENT: >>>
Independent verification of the deployment shall be performed for each
deployment instance after the deployment engineer's sign-off of the
deployment record (DM-060).

Verification scope:

  a) Deployment record (DM-060):
       - All mandatory fields completed.
       - Signed by both deployment engineer and supervising safety engineer.
       - Pre-deployment checks all confirmed satisfactory.
       - Post-write CRC and commissioning tests all PASS.
       - No unresolved deviations.

  b) Evidence completeness (DM-070):
       - All evidence items present, legible, and archived.
       - Tool output log consistent with the deployment record entries.

  c) Software version on target:
       - Query target system remotely or via diagnostic interface.
       - Confirm reported version matches the deployed release (SW-REL-xxx).

  d) Consistency with release note:
       - Release note (VAL-100 / APP-140) hash matches the hash recorded
         in DM-060.
       - Target hardware and bootloader versions match the release note
         prerequisites.

Verification method: structured inspection by the Deployment Verifier,
independent of the deployment engineer, using a checklist derived from
EN 50716:2023, Clause 9.1 and this Deployment Manual.
Verifier: <Name, Organisation, independence evidence>
Checklist reference: <document ID>
