[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Change record template

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: DM-160
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Change record (DCR) mandatory content
STATEMENT: >>>
Each change record (DCR-xxx) shall be an ACTION_ITEM node containing the
following information in its STATEMENT field:

  Change Request reference:  <CR-xxx>
  Change description:        <brief description of what is changed>
  Reason / trigger:          <defect ID / regulatory requirement / obsolescence /
                              field anomaly report / other>
  Maintenance category:      <Corrective / Adaptive / Perfective / Emergency>
  Classification:            <Major / Minor — per DM-110>
  Safety function affected:  <None / describe>

  Impact analysis summary (DM-140):
    Affected requirements:   <SRS-xxx, APP-xxx list / none>
    Affected components:     <component / file list>
    Regression test set:     <test case ID list>
    Hazard log update:       <Required / Not required>

  Implementation:
    Source files modified:   <filename, commit hash>
    Documents updated:       <document ID, revision>
    Compilation result:      <PASS — zero errors, zero warnings>
    Static analysis result:  <PASS / findings addressed>

  Testing:
    Test cases re-executed:  <ATR-xxx, VTR-xxx list>
    All tests PASS:          <Yes / No — if No, reference PR-DCR-xxx>
    Open problem reports:    <None / PR-DCR-xxx>

  Verification:
    Verifier:                <Name, Organisation>
    Verdict:                 <Approved / Not approved>
    Date:                    <YYYY-MM-DD>

The OWNER field shall name the Maintenance Implementer.
The DUE_DATE field shall be the agreed implementation completion date.
The COMMENT field shall record closure details: new release reference
(if Major) or maintenance record reference (if Minor).
<<<
