STATEMENT: >>>
The following DCR-xxx entries are the software change records for this
software item. Add one entry per approved change; set STATUS to Active during
implementation and Closed upon verification acceptance.
<<<

[ACTION_ITEM]
UID: DCR-001
STATUS: Closed
TITLE: Adaptive maintenance: update points response timeout for <station> following infrastructure upgrade
STATEMENT: >>>
Change Request reference:  CR-001
Change description:        The electromechanical points at <station> have been
  replaced with new motorised units (type <Mxx>) as part of an infrastructure
  upgrade. The new units have a faster verified response time of <n> ms,
  replacing the previous <n+x> ms units. The points timeout parameter in the
  application data must be updated to reflect the new infrastructure; the
  existing value is valid but overly conservative, and operational staff have
  reported unnecessary safe-state activations when the new points move faster
  than the existing timeout window triggers.
Reason / trigger:          Infrastructure upgrade; field anomaly report
  <FAR-012> citing spurious safe-state activations at <station>.
Maintenance category:      Adaptive
Classification:            Minor — affects a non-safety timing parameter
  within the permitted range (APP-C-004); no safety function behaviour
  changes; the new timeout value is less than the original and remains
  within the platform's verified range.

Impact analysis summary (DM-140):
  Affected requirements:   APP-C-004 (parameter range constraint); APP-F-003
    (approach locking logic — timeout is an input; confirmed: approach
    locking outcome unchanged within new timeout range).
  Affected components:     <parameters.dsl> (parameter table module, APP-070).
  Regression test set:     ATR-001 (route setting, covers points behaviour);
    ATR-xxx (approach locking release test — to be re-run).
  Hazard log update:       Not required — change is within analysed parameter
    range; no new hazard identified.

Implementation:
  Source files modified:   <parameters.dsl>, source revision <hash>.
  Documents updated:       APP-130 (baseline record) — Rev. B.
  Compilation result:      PASS — zero errors, zero warnings.
  Static analysis result:  PASS — no new MISRA violations.

Testing:
  Test cases re-executed:  ATR-001, ATR-xxx (approach locking).
  All tests PASS:          Yes.
  Open problem reports:    None.

Verification:
  Verifier:                <Name, Organisation>
  Verdict:                 Approved
  Date:                    <YYYY-MM-DD>
<<<
OWNER: <Maintenance Implementer Name>
DUE_DATE: <YYYY-MM-DD>
COMMENT: >>>
Change implemented in application data source revision <hash>. New compiled
baseline <APP-BL-yyy> generated and validated. Minor modification: no new
release note required; maintenance records updated in DM-170 (revision B of
APP-130). Deployed to <station> on <YYYY-MM-DD> per deployment record
<DR-STATION-yyyymmdd-01>. Spurious safe-state activations ceased following
deployment; confirmed by operations staff after <n> days of observation.
<<<

