[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Verification scope and method

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: DM-190
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Maintenance verification scope and method
STATEMENT: >>>
Independent verification shall be performed for each change record (DCR-xxx)
before it is closed, and a consolidated verification report issued at each
software release.

Per-change verification scope (for each DCR):

  a) Impact analysis (DM-140):
       - Impact analysis reviewed and found complete.
       - Classification (Major / Minor) is correct per DM-110.
       - Regression test set is consistent with affected requirements.

  b) Implementation:
       - Source changes are limited to the scope agreed in the DCR.
       - All modified source files committed to version control.
       - Compilation result: zero errors, zero warnings.
       - Static analysis results acceptable.

  c) Testing:
       - All regression test cases from the impact analysis set executed.
       - All executed test cases show PASS verdict.
       - No open Critical or Major problem reports.

  d) Documentation:
       - All affected lifecycle documents updated.
       - Traceability maintained from changed requirements to modified source
         to re-executed test cases.

Per-release consolidated verification scope (for Major modifications):

  e) All DCRs in the release are closed with Approved verdict.
  f) Re-validation evidence is complete (DM-130).
  g) Maintenance records (DM-170, DM-180) are up to date.
  h) New release note is issued and consistent with the software baseline.

Verification method: structured inspection by the Maintenance Verifier,
independent of the Maintenance Implementer, using a checklist derived from
EN 50716:2023, Clause 9.2.
Verifier: <Name, Organisation, independence evidence>
Checklist reference: <document ID>
<<<
